# LISENBART — pre-launch checklist

When the site is in **final development stage** or the user mentions **deploying, uploading to hosting, going live, or launch readiness**, proactively remind them about **Formspree** (contact form is not wired yet).

## Formspree — still TODO

Contact forms on `index.html`, `original.html`, and `services.html` currently **mock-submit** in `www/js/main.js` (shows success without sending).

Before launch:
1. Create a Formspree form and get the endpoint URL (`https://formspree.io/f/XXXX`).
2. In `www/js/main.js`, replace the mock block with real submit — comment at ~line 142: set `form.action` and call `form.submit()` (or `fetch` to Formspree).
3. Test success/error UX on all three pages and all languages.
4. Confirm hidden fields work: `source`, `_subject`, `_replyto`, `page_url` (built by `prepareContactFormPayload`).

Do not wire Formspree early unless the user asks; **do remind** when hosting/deployment is discussed.
